******
[2] North Dakota
Date: Mon 30 Jul 2012
Source: Grand Forks (ND) Herald [edited]
http://www.grandforksherald.com/event/article/id/241764/group/homepage/


North Dakota health officials also are seeing a spike in cases of whooping cough, said Abbi Pierce, immunization surveillance coordinator in the Division of Disease Control, North Dakota Department of Health. So far in 2012, North Dakota has more cases of whooping cough than were reported in all of 2011. As of 23 Jul 2012, the health department has received reports of 79 cases, already surpassing 2011's total of 70.

North Dakota is in sync with the national trend of sharply escalating numbers of whooping cough cases that is causing serious concern among health care professionals.

"Several states are reporting incredibly high numbers of cases this year [2012]," Pierce said. In North Dakota, "we're experiencing higher levels of cases but nowhere near the levels they're seeing in Minnesota and Washington State," she said.

North Dakota's highest number of whooping cough cases, 757, was recorded in 2004, Pierce said.

