******
[4] Maryland
Date: Sun 22 Jul 2012
Source: Cecil County (MD) Daily [edited]
http://www.cecildaily.com/news/local_news/article_ad08f7a6-d46c-11e1-9c05-0019bb2963f4.html


Maryland health officials say it appears whooping cough is on the rise. Kurt Seetoo, senior epidemiologist with the Maryland Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, said in 2011 there were 123 cases of the disease. In 2012, from 1 Jan 2012 to 30 Jun 2012, there have already been 133," Seetoo said of the preliminary numbers.

Seetoo said anyone who has contact with an infant should get immunized to prevent transmitting whooping cough. Family members, including grandparents, should get the booster, known as TDaP.

