[5] Montana
Date: Thu 26 Jul 2012
Source: Montana Department of Health [edited]
http://www.dphhs.mt.gov/publichealth/immunization/documents/MontanaPertussisUpdate.pdf


According to the DPHHS Communicable Disease Weekly Update (20 Jul 2012), so far in 2012, there have been 355 cases of pertussis in Montana, compared to 66 cases for the same period in 2011.

With school and athletics beginning soon, DPHHS is encouraging healthcare providers, schools, and sports teams to be aware of our continuing outbreak and consider the recommendations outlined on the attached information sheet.

